section.section:
Subject to the hearing provisions of § 4-311 of this subtitle, the Commission may deny a license to an applicant, reprimand a licensee, or suspend or revoke a license if the applicant or licensee:
fraudulently or deceptively obtains or attempts to obtain a license for the applicant or licensee or for another person;
fraudulently or deceptively uses a license;
violates this title; or
violates a regulation adopted under this title.

To determine the amount of the penalty imposed under this subsection, the Commission shall consider:
the seriousness of the violation;
the good faith of the violator;
any previous violations;
the assets of the violator; and
the harmful effect of the violation on the general public and the sporting industry.
